HEADWORD: dactylozooid
<hw>dac`tyl*o*zo"oid</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧k`t⟦icr⟧*l⟦osl⟧*z⟦omac⟧"oid)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>da`ktylos</grk> finger + E.
<ets>zooid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A kind of zooid of
Siphonophora which has an elongated or even vermiform body, with one
tentacle, but no mouth. See <er>Siphonophora</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

